<br>
To think its 'bad' or 'good' is just silly. These calendars were started pre-kunark (or at most a short ways into kunark) when there was a limited number of places for an uberguild to go. (five, to be exact).<br>
<br>
Now, for the 50+ set, there are: 5 planes, TOV, Veeshan's Peak, Trakanon, 4 Outdoor Kunark Dragons, the Hole, Kael, Skyshrine, Western Wastes, Chardok, Old Seb, Howling Stones (aka Charasis), Upstairs City of Mist, etc etc etc.<br>
<br>
I know for a fact that there is always a place to go and if you're good, you always go where you want.<br>
<br>
EVERY guild but one that has released the sleeper did it in reaction to another guild being close to Farming the Warders. Simple economics: You get your kicks from being able to do things first, you keep the ability to do things first by ALWAYS being first. By perma-killing the warders, you are slowing down your competitors. Any uberguild (but the one) that claims otherwise is either lying to you or themselves.<br>
<br>
No offense to the other hardcore RP'ers on this server... but this setting isn't worth a steam-pan full of warm stool as a RP setting. It is generic, trite, boring, and overdone. Getting bent about Gnomes, Halflings, Elves, etc having or not having RP reasons to do something is just delusional. This is NOT a creative setting, it is a generic setting... you can ASSUME a RP reason exists because the 'hard and fast' rules are illogical, unrealistic, and are flags of disbelief of themselves.<br>
<br>
If you want an RP setting, ditch some of the wierd races and deal instead with some real motives and real stories. Cheezy gods and bizarre religions do not a good setting make. <p>Nakath<BR>
The Esoteric Order</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rexfelix>Rexfelix</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 63<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 6:03:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: about calendars and the sleeper and maybe a little about</span><hr size=1> Hehe Nakath,<br>
